{"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"HashFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":" = "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GHashFunc","text":"GHashFunc"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The function is passed a key and should return a "},{"code":"guint","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" hash value.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The functions "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_direct_hash()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_int_hash()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_str_hash()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" provide","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"hash functions which can be used when the key is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gpointer"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gint"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gchar"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" respectively.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_direct_hash()"},{"text":" is also the appropriate hash function for keys","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the form ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GINT_TO_POINTER (n)"},{"type":"text","text":" (or similar macros)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A good hash functions should produce"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"hash values that are evenly distributed over a fairly large range.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The modulus is taken with the hash table size (a prime number) to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"find the ‘bucket’ to place each key into. The function should also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be very fast, since it is called for each key lookup.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the hash functions provided by GLib have these qualities,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"but are not particularly robust against manufactured keys that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"cause hash collisions. Therefore, you should consider choosing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a more secure hash function when using a GHashTable with keys","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that originate in untrusted data (such as HTTP requests).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Using "},{"code":"g_str_hash()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in that situation might make your application","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"vulnerable to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/lwn.net\/Articles\/474912\/","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The key to choosing a good hash is unpredictability.  Even"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"cryptographic hashes are very easy to find collisions for when the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remainder is taken modulo a somewhat predictable prime number.  There","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"must be an element of randomness that an attacker is unable to guess."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"HashFunc","symbolKind":"typealias","externalID":"s:4GLib8HashFunca","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Type Alias","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"HashFunc"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind